You'll find an RStudio file containing the following exercise, as well as an Excel file
that explains the exercise step by step and a PDF file where the ideas are laid out more clearly.

Calculate, showing all working, the annual nominal rate of interest convertible quarterly that is
equivalent to:
a. an effective rate of interest of 4% per half-year,
b. a nominal rate of interest of 6% p.a. convertible monthly,
c. a nominal rate of discount of 6% p.a. convertible every 3 years.
